00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 15=

19
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:43,360
Master Qiu.

20
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,440
Getting water?

21
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:50,460
(Hot water)

22
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,740
He's throwing his weight around,

23
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:57,000
just because he's related
to Huang Zhengjing.

24
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:59,720
He's completely unreasonable.

25
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:03,846
Just don't stoop to his level.

26
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:05,120
What?

27
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,720
They really let him be the chef?

28
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,880
The guy is just bluffing.

29
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:10,280
What Chang'an Restaurant?

30
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,480
I asked around.

31
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:15,000
He just chops veggies in a tiny diner.

32
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,600
Keep your voice down.

33
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:21,960
I bet those salty steamed buns last time

34
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:24,520
were tampered with by that jerk.

35
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,720
Don't talk nonsense.

36
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,600
You can't accuse him without proof.

37
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,040
Fine, I'm talking nonsense.

38
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:47,040
Qiu, don't feel pressured.

39
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:49,080
I'm fine either way.

40
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,320
Qing'e.

41
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,360
Come in.

42
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,840
Check out my knife skills.

43
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:00,600
Don't go.

44
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,560
Hot pan, cold oil.

45
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,360
Stir-fried shredded potatoes.

46
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,840
Master Liao, Master Liao!

47
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:16,000
Too much, too much oil!

48
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,760
Scallions to bring out the aroma.

49
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:21,320
If you keep cooking like that,

50
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:23,400
we'll be broke
for the rest of the month.

51
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,560
Not a drop of oil left.

52
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,880
Here comes the shredded potatoes.

53
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,000
Cooking takes real skill.

54
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,680
Ignore that amateur's nonsense.

55
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:32,920
See how I do it.

56
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,360
What a mess.

57
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:37,040
How's that?

58
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:45,760
Hurry, hurry. Your waist.

59
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,600
Straighten up. Keep it straight.

60
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,600
Keep your legs tight.

61
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,400
Stand straight in life.

62
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,880
Performing opera is about people.

63
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,920
If your back isn't straight,

64
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:05,080
you'll look all limp onstage.

65
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,880
Wriggling like a snake up there.

66
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,280
It'll be disgusting.

67
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:15,280
Our opera stars,

68
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:19,880
such as Mi Lan and Hua Caixiang,

69
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,960
are not Dan roles at all.

70
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:23,960
Once they step onstage,

71
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,720
their bodies sag,

72
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:30,360
hips drop, and legs sink.

73
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,640
Such a waste of their pretty faces.

74
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:37,560
Do you think the audience
comes for faces?

75
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:41,280
They come for basic skills
and the opera.

76
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,040
The streets are full of faces.

77
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:49,040
Back then, among the Cun generation,

78
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:52,440
there were so many
great Northwest stars.

79
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:55,720
First, we had a great master.

80
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,200
Second...

81
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:02,920
Second, we could endure hardship.

82
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:05,920
Splits, backbend, and handstand.

83
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:08,200
Not to mention the carpet work.

84
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,320
Where were the carpets?

85
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:13,800
We tumbled on the bare yellow earth.

86
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:18,040
Do you know how we practiced
the circular walk?

87
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,920
Master made us balance a book
on our heads.

88
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:24,200
He stood there with a cane.

89
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,280
If the book fell,

90
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,640
we got caned.

91
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,240
We also got caned

92
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:32,320
for walking too slowly,

93
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:35,920
twisting our waist,

94
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:40,120
and shaking our heads.

95
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,280
After a day of the circular walk,

96
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,480
we were covered in bloody welts.

97
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,560
We were covered...

98
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:15,800
Qing'e.

99
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,400
Master Liao, you're still up?

100
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,200
Where have you been?

101
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,000
Nowhere.

102
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:32,000
You go to the theater every day.

103
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,280
What are you doing there?

104
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,240
I've been watching you for a while.

105
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:51,480
Are you learning opera

106
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,480
with that old gatekeeper?

107
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:53,920
What?

108
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,560
You want to leave the kitchen?

109
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,760
Lately,

110
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,400
you've seen it.

111
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,880
I work as the chef.

112
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,240
Everyone praises my cooking, right?

113
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:04,840
So, don't go anywhere.

114
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,386
Just learn cooking from me.

115
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,400
Here.

116
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:10,910
- Rock sugar.
- I don't want it.

117
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,000
You eat it.

118
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,320
No, I don't want it!

119
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,240
Keep your voice down.

120
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:18,240
Hey, slow down, kid.

121
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:19,720
Slow down.

122
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,040
Get to bed early, okay?

123
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,680
One day, I'll get you candy.

124
00:08:15,340 --> 00:08:18,140
(Keep things clean)

125
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,520
So annoying.

126
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:04,460
(Hot water)

127
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,320
Where is that fool?

128
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,880
Still snoring and sleeping in.

129
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:22,880
Look at what he did.

130
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:26,440
He used half a month's oil in a week.

131
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,960
What about the rest of the month?

132
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,460
Don't worry.

133
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,880
This week: steamed buns and noodles.

134
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,040
Let's use less oil

135
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,880
and try to make it up.

136
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,960
That's not the point.

137
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:42,560
He took the cow and left you the stake.

138
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:43,640
The flame's too high.

139
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:44,880
The corn congee is sticking.

140
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,840
I'm not mad; you shouldn't be either.

141
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,320
Laidi, lower the heat.

142
00:09:58,460 --> 00:10:02,100
(Hot water)

143
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:13,600
Harder.

144
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:16,920
Use your waist like in training.

145
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,280
This dough.

146
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:26,870
Come on, push harder.

147
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,160
Master Song.

148
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:34,680
Are you free right now?

149
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,240
I was looking for you.

150
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:45,680
Cover it and let it rest a bit.

151
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,440
Then call two from the troupe.

152
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:49,200
Have them help make steamed buns.

153
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:52,000
I need a rest. I'm heading back.

154
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,360
Qing'e, come here.

155
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,440
Add some water.

156
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,040
Don't burn yourself.

157
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,080
What did you see?

158
00:11:42,406 --> 00:11:43,800
Tomatoes are almost out of season.

159
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,120
Make the tomato sauce, okay?

160
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:45,960
I haven't bought any.

161
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,520
- Too pricey.
- Why?

162
00:11:47,680 --> 00:11:48,690
- Too pricey.
- Pricey.

163
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:52,680
The troupe is buying tomatoes
for tomato sauce.

164
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:53,640
I'll take you with me.

165
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,000
Will it be cheaper?

166
00:12:00,290 --> 00:12:01,200
That's great.

167
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,680
I saw the sweater you knit for the kid.

168
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:05,840
That red one?

169
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,760
It's really nice.

170
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,840
Why are the edges curling?

171
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:12,000
Qing'e, we're short on wrappers.
Roll more.

172
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,480
Master Song, the filling's too salty.

173
00:12:16,293 --> 00:12:17,506
- Too salty.
- Leave it there.

174
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:18,520
Here.

175
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:19,760
Okay, here.

176
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,880
I'll knit it. Bring it here.

177
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,260
- It's nothing.
- Really.

178
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:28,200
Stop.

179
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:30,520
It's way too salty.

180
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,320
What a jerk.

181
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,840
Honestly, Master Song.

182
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,640
Can't you be more careful?

183
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,120
I'll do it next time.

184
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:44,000
Good thing we caught it early.

185
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:46,240
Or those opera singers would yell at us.

186
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:49,560
Those jerks can't even act well.

187
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:50,600
Oh, my goodness.

188
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:52,000
They're ruining the troupe,

189
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:54,000
yet they pick on us daily.

190
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,480
It makes me so mad.

191
00:12:58,680 --> 00:12:59,520
Why keep making them?

192
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:00,900
The filling is too salty.

193
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:05,700
(Hot water)

194
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:16,760
Laidi.

195
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:17,760
Master Song.

196
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:18,760
Say no more.

197
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,360
I know everything.

198
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,000
He's gone too far.

199
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,160
He's way too scheming

200
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:26,800
to tell right from wrong.

201
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:28,520
If this continues,

202
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,920
karma will get him.

203
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:33,360
It's okay to take a little loss.

204
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:36,520
Oh, right.

205
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:39,560
Keep this to yourself, okay?

206
00:13:39,773 --> 00:13:40,760
It won't do you any good.

207
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:42,160
I'll just be more careful.

208
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:43,920
Thanks.

209
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,440
Where are you off to now?

210
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,720
Going to practice flips again?

211
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,360
Don't go.

212
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:10,200
The fire's banked. I'm done here.

213
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,120
Why can't I go?

214
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,720
Why can't you go?

215
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,960
You're always with that old man,

216
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:17,953
calling it learning opera.

217
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:19,400
That old man

218
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,120
put his hands all over you all day.

219
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:23,080
Who knows what he's up to?

220
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:24,680
I'm the chef here.

221
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:25,840
I'm your boss.

222
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,760
What if something happens to you?

223
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,600
I'm responsible for you.

224
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,640
I promised Master Gou.

225
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:32,560
I can't quit halfway.

226
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,480
I'll finish him off.

227
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:00,840
Laidi.

228
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:02,000
Laidi.

229
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:03,400
Master Gou.

230
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:06,080
What are you doing? I was waiting.

231
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,440
Why haven't you gone?

232
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:13,320
Master Liao.

233
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,480
You old fool.

234
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:17,560
You came over here yourself.

235
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,320
Why are you cursing at me?

236
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:21,680
Cursing? That's letting you off easy.

237
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:24,360
Your hands reached
from the gatehouse to the kitchen.

238
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,480
Trying to poach my people?

239
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,240
I'm telling you.

240
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:28,640
There are over twenty kids there.

241
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:30,400
Find apprentices over there.

242
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:31,880
If you reach my kitchen again,

243
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,426
I'll chop you off and feed you to pigs.

244
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:35,800
You mean the kid learning opera?

245
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:38,000
She goes after you've damped the stove.

246
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,840
It doesn't affect the cooking.

247
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:41,520
What can she learn from you?

248
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:43,280
Oh, my gosh.

249
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:45,720
She should learn cooking from me.

250
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:48,480
She's made for performing opera.

251
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,200
She might make it one day.

252
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:52,760
I fear she'll cook here all her life.

253
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:54,040
That would bury his talent.

254
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:55,240
What's wrong with cooking?

255
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:57,320
What's wrong with cooking?

256
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,960
Opera singers used to be
in lower social strata.

257
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,360
Now, you're acting all fancy.

258
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:03,400
You're getting cocky, huh?

259
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:05,320
Food is the people's priority.

260
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:07,560
Do you think opera
matters more than food?

261
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,040
Fine.

262
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:11,920
You have a point.

263
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:15,880
The kid studies opera to make a living.

264
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,040
Let's talk this through calmly.

265
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,840
One more skill for the kid

266
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:22,640
can't be a bad thing, can it?

267
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:26,800
Even so, she shouldn't learn from you.

268
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,200
I know

269
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,240
what you're capable of.

270
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:32,400
As a man, you always play women.

271
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:33,960
All prissy and affected.

272
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,360
Not manly at all.

273
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:36,920
You'd only teach her

274
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:38,480
to be a vixen.

275
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:40,880
Oh, please.

276
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:43,520
Do you think you're really
Chef Liao now?

277
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,320
Shame on you.

278
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,600
You're a total embarrassment.

279
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:48,080
Why huff? You're driving me mad.

280
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:50,120
Back at that greasy roadside diner,

281
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:52,000
you just scrubbed pots and chopped veg.

282
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,120
Then you came here,

283
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:55,040
like a pig with scallions,
playing grand.

284
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,600
You can't even fake being refined.

285
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,640
You're just a bumpkin.

286
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:59,350
I'll teach you a lesson.

287
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,560
How could you hit me?

288
00:17:01,690 --> 00:17:02,640
I... you...

289
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:05,280
Ah, it hurts. It hurts!

290
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:07,080
Showing off moves with me now?

291
00:17:07,080 --> 00:17:08,720
You think you're clever, dumb hog?

292
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:09,800
I'll fight you for real!

293
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,580
Bring it on.

294
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,166
No, no. Whoa, why grab a tool?

295
00:17:13,177 --> 00:17:14,080
Let go. Give it to me.

296
00:17:14,080 --> 00:17:15,520
- Talk it out.
- It's okay.

297
00:17:15,840 --> 00:17:17,920
Just wait. I'll go to Director Huang.

298
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:19,080
Go to anyone. It won't help.

299
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:19,920
You hit me, huh?

300
00:17:20,773 --> 00:17:21,800
You want to be fired, huh?

301
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,160
- Keep it down.
- Remember this.

302
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:25,000
Neither of you will stay.

303
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,640
You only bully old men and kids.

304
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:29,320
You fool. Choke on your anger.

305
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:30,400
Just you wait.

306
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:31,880
You can't do this. You can't.

307
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:34,280
You'll ruin the child's future.

308
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,200
Don't be scared.

309
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,160
With trash like him, hit where it hurts.

310
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:39,280
Why should I care about her future?

311
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:41,720
Let the child go. I'll drop the ladle.

312
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,760
Master Liao! Master Liao!

313
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:44,440
What did you say?

314
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:48,120
If you let the child learn opera,

315
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:49,560
you can be the chef from now on.

316
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,120
I'll work under you.

317
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,440
I'll wash veg and dishes,

318
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,840
feed pigs, and tend the fire.

319
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,280
I'll do whatever

320
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:56,840
you tell me to do. Deal?

321
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,200
Master Gou, please don't be mad.

322
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:19,560
♪Expecting the bride♪

323
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:20,680
Zhou.

324
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:22,400
Bring me the staff.

325
00:18:23,280 --> 00:18:24,360
What do you need it for?

326
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:27,600
Master Gou just fought Master Liao.

327
00:18:30,060 --> 00:18:31,000
Did you lose?

328
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,240
Of course not.

329
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:33,680
Then why?

330
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,286
Master Liao won't let me learn opera.

331
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:37,320
That old coot.

332
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:39,040
I'll break his legs.

333
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,280
As if I'd need you to hit him.

334
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:48,800
I've thought it over.

335
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:52,680
Let's stage an introductory play,
Da Jiao Zan.

336
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:55,080
That's how we had our initiation.

337
00:18:55,939 --> 00:18:57,915
You'll teach her
how to use the staff and spear;

338
00:18:57,926 --> 00:18:59,932
I'll teach her posture, vocal style,
and dialogue.

339
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:01,720
What do you think?

340
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:02,920
Great.

341
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,080
Da Jiao Zan

342
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:09,400
is an opera excerpt from Yang Paifeng.

343
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:11,840
Yang Paifeng is a person's name.

344
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:14,280
She's about your age.

345
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:15,760
She was also a kitchen maid.

346
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,800
While she cooked by the stove,

347
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,520
she drilled martial arts foundation

348
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:23,280
and later led armies as a great general.

349
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,480
This opera excerpt has martial scenes.

350
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,200
It's perfect for initiation.

351
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:30,080
Martial scenes take real effort.

352
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:32,480
Be it a martial scene or a civil scene,

353
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,640
a martial arts foundation never hurts.

354
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,040
What's initiation?

355
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:47,480
Initiation

356
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:49,520
means the teacher drawing

357
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,680
the first stroke on a blank page.

358
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:00,040
Kid, remember this.

359
00:20:00,290 --> 00:20:01,220
Not good.

360
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,080
Go.

361
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:04,420
Good.

362
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:05,280
Don't drift too far.

363
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:06,280
Pick up the pace.

364
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:08,720
Throw the punch.

365
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:12,560
That's even worse.

366
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:14,040
Project the singing.

367
00:20:14,040 --> 00:20:15,620
(Remold, Rescue, Reform)
One, two, one.

368
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,320
(Education)
One, one.

369
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:18,880
Aim to reform.

370
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:20,480
Right.

371
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,420
Go.

372
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:22,280
Turn around. Pose.

373
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:24,960
Still not good.

374
00:21:10,180 --> 00:21:15,880
♪The couple was separated by death♪

375
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:22,790
♪The deepest pain in this world♪

376
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:25,620
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

377
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:38,510
♪In the first month, sorrow was♪

378
00:21:38,870 --> 00:21:42,490
♪Buried deep inside my chest♪

379
00:21:42,890 --> 00:21:46,280
♪Tonight, the moon is veiled in mist♪

380
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:47,200
Sign in.

381
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:51,400
♪The land lies still and silent♪

382
00:21:51,850 --> 00:21:57,960
♪The lonely wilds feel cold and bleak♪

383
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:58,880
Who are you here for?

384
00:22:02,970 --> 00:22:07,750
♪Cries for my wife♪

385
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:11,280
Zhou Ren Hui Fu!

386
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,400
My old friend!

387
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:18,120
I thought you died and became a ghost.

388
00:22:18,346 --> 00:22:19,960
On Tomb-Sweeping Day,
at Master's grave,

389
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,466
I nearly burned offerings for him too.

390
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:25,960
Where have you been all these years?

391
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:27,653
How did you make it through?

392
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:30,040
In the mountain gullies

393
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:31,720
of Xifu, Gansu, and Ningxia,

394
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:35,360
out in those remote, poor villages,

395
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:38,160
I went from village to village,

396
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:42,280
singing opera for meals where I could.

397
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,120
Then why not stay out there as a stray?

398
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:46,280
Why come back?

399
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,640
Don't steal our meal, okay?

400
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:48,960
We're very protective of our food.

401
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:52,840
Let's get serious.

402
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,000
That out-of-town troupe

403
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:57,600
is doing the old opera

404
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,560
with real drive and precision.

405
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:02,080
We old hands of the Cun generation

406
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:04,680
should show our voices too, right?

407
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:07,920
Pour some more.

408
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,400
Pour it. Pour it.

409
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:11,560
Who's this kid?

410
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:15,200
A relative's kid. He's an orphan.

411
00:23:15,680 --> 00:23:16,640
His name is Situan.

412
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:18,200
He's been with me for years.

413
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:21,520
Half my apprentice, half my son.

414
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:24,200
So, he's your apprentice. Cheers.

415
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:25,880
Apprentice.

416
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:27,240
Good apprentice.

417
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,520
Come on. Come on.

418
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:30,400
Master Gou.

419
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:32,200
Come here, kid.

420
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,680
Hu Sanyuan's niece.

421
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:37,280
She's an apprentice to all three of us.

422
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:39,480
Where's Hu Sanyuan?

423
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:41,560
- He's left.
- Where to?

424
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:42,920
I'll tell you later.

425
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,480
I told you before.

426
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:47,920
What are the names of the Cun brothers?

427
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:50,920
Ren, Yi, Li, Zhi, Xin.

428
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:52,960
Wen, Liang, Gong, Jian, Rang.

429
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:55,320
Xiao, Ti, Jie, Shu, Yong.

430
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:57,960
Zhong, Hou, Shang, Qin, Jing.

431
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:00,600
What are the names of the living?

432
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:02,600
Zhong, Xiao, Ren, and Yi.

433
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:05,600
He's Xiao.

434
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:06,920
Call him Master Gu.

435
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:10,440
Go on. Greet Master Gu. Offer wine.

436
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:14,960
Master Gu, please have some wine.

437
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:17,200
Zhong, Xiao, Ren, and Yi are all here.

438
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:18,360
Good.

439
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:26,880
Hu Sanyuan's niece.

440
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:27,960
Let me tell you.

441
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:32,000
I spotted your uncle's gift for drums.

442
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:34,400
That's why he learned, got it?

443
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:35,840
Kid,

444
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:37,560
Master Gu is really something.

445
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,880
The top Wusheng role
of the Cun generation.

446
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:43,960
His civil scenes match
his martial scenes.

447
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:46,400
A big-name opera star back then.

448
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:50,400
Everyone wanted him in Chang'an Troupe.

449
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:52,360
Across the Five Northwestern Provinces,

450
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:55,240
he performed everywhere.

451
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:56,520
He's truly impressive.

452
00:24:56,520 --> 00:24:59,280
- He knows hundreds of plays.
- Yes.

453
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:00,560
Do Da Jiao Zan in a bit.

454
00:25:00,560 --> 00:25:02,520
Let Master Gu give you some pointers.

455
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:03,400
Come on, come on.

456
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:04,250
- Okay.
- Come on.

457
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:15,520
You hit the kid on the head.

458
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:32,560
Say something.

459
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:47,440
The truth or a nice lie?

460
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:49,200
Speak plainly.

461
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,240
Fine.

462
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:57,640
The kid's staff work is excellent.

463
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:59,560
You can tell at a glance

464
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,840
that Zhou Cunren taught her.

465
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,813
What about the posture and vocal style?

466
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,480
I spaced out for a second.

467
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:12,360
It was like seeing

468
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:14,520
you back in the day.

469
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:16,520
Kid,

470
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:19,040
Master Gu praised you. Say thanks.

471
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:20,600
Thank you, Master Gu.

472
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:22,520
How old are you?

473
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:24,160
Seventeen.

474
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:26,200
Seventeen.

475
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:29,000
Training under someone in his sixties,

476
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:32,160
you've built real skill

477
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:37,160
and picked up his old-fashioned air.

478
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:44,080
What do you mean by that?

479
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:50,880
Kid,

480
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,960
how old is Yang Paifeng?

481
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:57,120
Sixteen or seventeen.

482
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,840
But on stage,

483
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:01,480
I didn't see a 16- or 17-year-old

484
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:04,560
lively and cute kitchen maid.

485
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:07,480
All I saw was a mature

486
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:11,640
and steady heroine.

487
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:12,840
You mean

488
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:14,840
the kid didn't act lively or cute?

489
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:17,360
Not lively or cute enough,

490
00:27:17,360 --> 00:27:20,240
but way too calm.

491
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:23,640
Yang Paifeng is a kitchen maid.

492
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:25,640
Poor kids grow up fast.

493
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,720
She's no rich lady or princess

494
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:29,366
who never worries about food or clothes,

495
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:31,440
or gets doted on by her parents,

496
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,040
spending all day thinking

497
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:35,160
about how to be naughty or act cute.

498
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:37,560
Then why, back then, did you act

499
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:39,480
with your eyes darting around,

500
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:42,600
bouncing around like a little deer?

501
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:44,033
I was beaten by Master.

502
00:27:44,044 --> 00:27:45,400
Master didn't hit you hard enough.

503
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:48,280
You know squat.
You don't know the Dan role.

504
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,560
Why ask me if you won't listen?

505
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:52,000
A leopard can't change its spots.

506
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,960
You only want to hear flattery.

507
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,600
You never have anything nice to say.

508
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:01,040
Is this really necessary?

509
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:02,200
It's been so many years.

510
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,760
You miss each other when apart,

511
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:06,400
but bicker every time you meet.

512
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:08,440
You didn't bicker enough in your youth?

513
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:12,400
Sorry, I didn't perform well.

514
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:15,240
You did great. Really great.

515
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:17,440
You're not wrong. It's not your fault.

516
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,080
Alright, stop talking.

517
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:21,080
I'm turning off the lights. Let's go.

518
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:13,480
Am I old-fashioned?

519
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,520
What does old-fashioned mean?

520
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:20,360
Go home and look in the mirror.

521
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:22,840
Practice being lively and cute.

522
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:50,840
You're hopeless.

523
00:29:50,840 --> 00:29:52,000
You can't even do cute.

524
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:20,920
Hu Sanyuan.

525
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:23,000
Here.

526
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:24,720
Report to Captain Zhang at the office.

527
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:25,560
Yes.

528
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:42,840
(Qinqiang opera: Zhan Shan Tong)
♪With one roar, I'm bound outside♪

529
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:44,160
Captain Zhang.

530
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,380
Hu Sanyuan is here.

531
00:31:45,380 --> 00:31:46,320
Report.

532
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:47,160
Come in.

533
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,320
Go on in.

534
00:31:50,600 --> 00:31:51,640
How was my singing?

535
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:53,680
You're the pro here.

536
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,280
Give us your thoughts.

537
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:57,560
Captain Zhang, it was great.

538
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:59,680
How so? Tell me.

539
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:03,200
Even troupe pros avoid Zhan Shan Tong.

540
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:04,200
Yet you dare to sing it.

541
00:32:04,760 --> 00:32:05,600
Why?

542
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:07,440
It takes serious vocal skill.

543
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:09,040
It's easy to go off-key.

544
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:10,880
Did I go off-key?

545
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,040
Tell me the truth.

546
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:17,480
Captain Zhang,

547
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:19,920
you sang it with your own style.

548
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:21,400
What style?

549
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:22,780
No one would recognize it.

550
00:32:23,120 --> 00:32:25,140
Captain Zhang, you asked for honesty.

551
00:32:25,140 --> 00:32:26,140
Go.

552
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:27,000
Yes, sir.

553
00:32:27,780 --> 00:32:28,680
Come back.

554
00:32:28,680 --> 00:32:29,520
Here.

555
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:31,760
Here's the thing.

556
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:34,440
Teach me a piece everyone can recognize.

557
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:36,800
I'm joining

558
00:32:36,800 --> 00:32:39,160
the Provincial Prison System
Art Showcase.

559
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:40,920
Let's try to bring back

560
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:42,800
the first prize. What do you think?

561
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:46,100
What are you mumbling about?

562
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:51,153
(Education, Reform, Rescue)
Report: Hu Sanyuan is back.

563
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:57,550
- Rejoin the team.
- Yes.

564
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:08,520
Why are you back?

565
00:33:11,040 --> 00:33:11,880
What's that about?

566
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:13,680
Nothing good.

567
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:16,040
It must be another

568
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:17,659
Qinqiang opera jam with you.

569
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:19,600
Notice.

570
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:24,240
(Turn over a new leaf)
A showcase is coming.

571
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:26,360
Inmates with Qinqiang opera talent

572
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:29,440
or music and singing skills

573
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:31,840
are encouraged to sign up

574
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:33,080
and take part in the auditions.

575
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:36,880
They'll join correctional officers

576
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:40,080
to form a top performance troupe

577
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:42,400
representing Beishan Prison

578
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:46,480
in the Provincial Prison System
Art Showcase.

579
00:33:46,840 --> 00:33:47,880
That is all.

580
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,480
- Hu Sanyuan!
- Here!

581
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:56,320
Step forward.

582
00:33:58,240 --> 00:33:59,560
Except for the Women's Detachment,

583
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:02,880
(Education, Reform, Rescue)
everyone who can play

584
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:03,760
or sing is here.

585
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:05,560
Select from them

586
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,480
and form a decent troupe

587
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,240
to join the showcase.

588
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:11,320
Bring me back the first prize.

589
00:34:11,680 --> 00:34:13,920
Captain, what if we can't?

590
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:15,560
Then get a second prize.

591
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:18,040
At least get a third prize.

592
00:34:18,200 --> 00:34:20,440
If you win, I'll record your merits.

593
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:36,820
(Turn over a new leaf;
Embrace a new life)

594
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:37,840
Hu Sanyuan!

595
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:38,880
Here!

596
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:40,920
I got all these instruments

597
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:42,880
exactly according to your list.

598
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:45,680
I did my part.

599
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:48,600
Now, it's your turn.

600
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:49,880
Yes.

601
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:51,400
Okay.

602
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:53,160
Start practicing.

603
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:35,420
(Turn over a new leaf;
Embrace a new life)

604
00:35:53,300 --> 00:36:00,300
(Notice, Wang Jianmin, Letters)

605
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:03,320
Master Gou, did you call me?

606
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,593
Drink that bowl of chicken soup.

607
00:36:06,640 --> 00:36:07,640
You have it.

608
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:09,520
Drink it when I tell you to.

609
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:17,400
What's so funny?

610
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:20,080
When you head back later, take that pot

611
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,000
of chicken soup to Master Gu.

612
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,920
Master Gu was right that night.

613
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:37,760
I made you too old-fashioned.

614
00:36:38,520 --> 00:36:40,440
I didn't even realize it
until he said it.

615
00:36:41,680 --> 00:36:43,080
I just didn't learn well.

616
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:46,560
That's just you being old-fashioned.

617
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:48,600
Don't take the blame for everything.

618
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:52,080
Have some soup.

619
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:00,760
You're too withdrawn, kid.

620
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:02,880
Hang out with the trainee class kids.

621
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:04,640
Have some fun with them.

622
00:37:04,640 --> 00:37:06,200
Sing a little, dance a little.

623
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:07,840
Look at those roller skates.

624
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:09,080
You should try them too.

625
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:12,080
Go shopping, catch a movie with them.

626
00:37:12,080 --> 00:37:13,840
Change things a bit.

627
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,440
All day in that ragged apron,

628
00:37:16,840 --> 00:37:18,400
with greasy and grimy sleeve covers.

629
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:21,200
Buy yourself a few pretty outfits.

630
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,600
Learn to dress yourself up.

631
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:24,280
A young girl's face

632
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:26,000
shouldn't be dirty and messy all day.

633
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:27,640
Wash up more often.

634
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:30,200
But I have work to do.

635
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:35,360
Fine.

636
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,400
Forget what I said.

637
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:45,640
(She was never treated like a girl.)

638
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:49,680
(All her life,
she was taught to endure.)

639
00:37:49,760 --> 00:37:53,680
(No one taught her how to be a girl.)

640
00:37:54,320 --> 00:37:55,880
(Master Gou told her to make friends.)

641
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:57,440
(How could she possibly know?)

642
00:37:57,760 --> 00:38:01,200
(This was harder for Yi Qing'e)

643
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:04,040
(than 1,000 vertical leg-holds
and 10,000 flips.)

644
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:48,040
Come on, kid. Have a bowl too.

645
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:49,760
I already had some.

646
00:38:50,400 --> 00:38:51,280
Then have another.

647
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:53,080
It'll warm you up. Come on.

648
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:55,720
Save it for Master Zhou.

649
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:59,880
Gou's soup is really good.

650
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:03,520
Your master is wasted at the gate.

651
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:05,760
He should cook in the cafeteria.

652
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:12,000
Your uncle was a good man, too.

653
00:39:13,440 --> 00:39:14,280
Such a shame.

654
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:19,000
He was
the most gifted drum master I knew.

655
00:39:20,240 --> 00:39:22,520
I remember when he first learned drums.

656
00:39:23,080 --> 00:39:26,400
His master only had to give him a hint,

657
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,400
and he'd make the drums sound magical.

658
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:32,960
Later, his master actually regretted it,

659
00:39:32,960 --> 00:39:35,200
saying that by teaching him,

660
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:36,560
he put himself out of a job.

661
00:39:36,833 --> 00:39:38,179
That's how awesome your uncle is.

662
00:39:43,680 --> 00:39:44,920
Don't overthink it.

663
00:39:46,040 --> 00:39:48,680
It's a blessing in disguise for you.

664
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:52,800
Gou is the best Dan role I've ever seen.

665
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:54,400
Back in the day,

666
00:39:55,520 --> 00:39:57,920
his fame spread for hundreds of miles.

667
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:02,040
Just wait till he plays Li Huiniang.

668
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:02,960
You'll see.

669
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:06,520
His makeup, posture, movement,

670
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:08,440
and vocal style

671
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:10,440
are amazing.

672
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:13,440
You'll completely forget he's a man.

673
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:18,840
Master Gu.

674
00:40:21,299 --> 00:40:22,939
How do I practice being lively and cute?

675
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:31,160
Being lively and cute comes from within.

676
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:32,880
If it's just practiced,

677
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:35,000
it's not cute at all.

678
00:41:30,460 --> 00:41:33,940
(Rehearsal Hall, Weed through the old
to bring forth the new)

679
00:42:00,440 --> 00:42:01,426
What are you looking at?

680
00:42:02,960 --> 00:42:03,880
Who are you hitting?

681
00:42:03,880 --> 00:42:04,720
Chu Jiahe.

682
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:08,320
Come on, come on.

683
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

684
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:10,520
I'm reporting it to the county.

685
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:11,720
We'll do Bi Shang Liang Shan.

686
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:13,200
You're back.

687
00:43:13,600 --> 00:43:15,360
Now, I feel a lot better.

688
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:18,280
Let's welcome our four directors.

689
00:43:20,160 --> 00:43:21,000
Director?

690
00:43:21,040 --> 00:43:22,440
A sweeper, a shopper, a gatekeeper.

691
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:23,626
How did they become directors?

692
00:43:23,720 --> 00:43:26,000
They'll show us their best tricks.

693
00:43:26,240 --> 00:43:27,240
What's there to see?

694
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:28,440
Go light the stove.

695
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:30,400
Some people say you four

696
00:43:30,440 --> 00:43:31,840
can't direct a play at all.

697
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

698
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

699
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

700
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

701
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

702
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

703
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

704
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

705
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

706
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

707
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

708
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

709
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

710
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

711
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

712
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

713
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

714
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

715
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

716
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

717
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

